Description: Fragment of oval handle of a pottery transport amphora, moderate turn. Clay medium, micaceous, dark red-brown; mixed inclusions. Oval(?) stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Pencil '49a'. Petrie noted several such stamps in his 1884-5 diary (EES Archive XVII 47). The oval section of the handle seems later than the run of pieces in the Zenon group.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1333)
